REFTEXT: This is a military/political police detachment, ensuring every soldier is doing his duty it also boost the presence of unsteady units on the battlefield in term of influence."

Friendly units within range of this squad won't surrender and will get their influence set at maximuum unless this squad is panique (moreover, all penalties in the case of Disheartened troops are removed).

This unit is made up either of raw conscripts, war-weary or unwilling soldiers.They will fight as any other, but will take +25% suppression damage in their territory and at most 75% as regular troops."

Disheartened units have a 25% suppression bonus in their territory but have 1/6 less maximum suppression than regular infantry units, morever they have half the influence compared to other infantry units. Thus military police or leader are required to make the most of these poorly motivated squads

Airborne training is particulary harsh and demanding, it prepares them for the airborne operations in which they will get airdrop in hostile territory, the men part of these squads have greater tolerance towards ennemy fire as a result.
Airbornes units get a greater maximum threshold for suppression compared to other infantry units 1/6, as well as a better suppression regen ratio.
Trained (1 star) recon units with awareness trait can grant this unit a moderate increase in range
The unit has the lv1 bonus increases range of all weapons of the unit by up to 125m if the unit is within the recon units peremiter
Trained (1 star), Veteran(2 stars) recon units with awareness trait can grant this unit decent increased range
The unit has Lv1 and lv2 bonus which increases range of all weapons of the unit by up to 250m if the unit is within the recon units effect peremiter
Trained (1 star), Veteran(2 stars), Elite (3 stars) recon units with awareness trait can grant this unit a considerable increase in range
The unit has lv1, lv2 and the lv3 bonus which increase range of all weapons of the unit by up to 375m if the unit is within the recon units peremiter

The second cope battles are harsh in term of vehicle casuality, recovery vehicle allow to capture unmanned vehicle and bunkers on the battlefield when they have a set level of  veterancy. Their efficiency at recovering vehicle scales with veterancy
The ability radius is at vet 1 150m, vet 2 200m, vet 3 250m, the time to capture is 40 seconds for vet 1, 25 seconds for vet 2, and 10 seconds for vet 3. Speed is also increased by veterancy
Recon vehicle can coordinates with nearby AT or Support vehicle to reach their optimum range efficiency on the battlefield. They give an extra range depending on the recon unit veterancy

The range bonus is of 125m for each veterancy rank up to vet 3. {Vet 1 has effect on [All tanks, All tank destroyers, All assault guns]} {Vet2 has effect on [Heavy tank destroyers, Medium and Heavy Assault guns, Long Range tanks] {Vet 3 has effect on [Heavy Assault guns]}, accuracy is compensated, radius also scales with veterancy like for leaders
Recon infantry can coordinates with nearby  AT or Support guns to reach their optimum range efficiency on the battlefield. they give them an extra range depending on the recon unit veterancy

The range bonus is of 125m for each veterancy rank up to vet 3. {Vet 1 has effect on [All AT guns, All supports guns]}, {Vet2 has effect on Heavy/long range AT guns, All support guns] {Vet 3 has effect on [All support guns]}.  Accuracy is compensated, radius also scales with veterancy like for leaders

Motorized open top anti tank units  are generally not as armored and sturdy as the tanks they hunt themsleves even if they have generaly good mobility, to couterbalance this they have to rely on their optics and ambush capacity to get the killing shot.

After 40 seconds at the same spot they get a passive ambush capacity that last for 120s giving them 5% more accuracy, there is a couldown of 30s, independantly of this capacity their stealth scales with veterancy.  TD units can't activate this capacity while engaged or when ennemy units are bellow 750m while they are ambush they can't use the "attack move" orders either

The men parts of these recons units have aquired the capacity to use their weapon to their outmost potential through their harsh spec ops training or battle exeperience, the more experience they have the more deadly they get at range. Their recons training makes them harder to dislodge from the battlefield.
Elite Combat Recon weapon range scales with veterancy 15% at vet 1 25% at vet 2 33% at vet 3, the unit also has a 25% damage resistance

This unit will never surrender. Fanatical units can also be ordered to stand fast for a last stand, they will fight to their last breath trading 25% damage resistance for 50% of suppression resistance, it gains a additional veterancy level but won't move nor retreat

This unit doesn't suffer suppression malus when behind ennemy lines. ALL raider unit have 50% Stealth bonus. Commando units can also be ordered to infitrate enemy line slowing down by one third but suppressing totaly their influence for 300 seconds

These units are armed civilians, mot only less effective at range. Contrary to ordinary troop they do not profit from greater mobility through experience, to remove the combat penalty they have to be close to a leader or other infantry. They take additional damage from ennemy fire the more stressed they are.

This unit suffers 10% accuracy and 15% fire rate penalty, their speed do not scale with veterancy, this last effect can not be removed through allied (120m) or leader influence. When stressed from 0.65 suppression onward they take 5%  more damage,  10% from 0.8 and so they have only 15% damage resistance while pinned down contrary to 25% for other infantry units. The resistance and speed penalty can't be removed.

These units excel in cqc combat situations, once in range they quicly gain the advantage over their ennemy through their tactics and training makes with short range submachine guns and grenades and makes them harder to pin and target.
Units with this trait will gain a 10% suppression resilience 10% damage resistance and a 15% aim time bonus once it's near ennnemy units(120m), their stealth is affected by veterancy.

Artillery Leader are not primerly made for frontline duty they allow you to reduce the min and max dispersion of your artillery guns and their aim time. They still give an advantageous rate of fire bonus to all ground units but no longuer influence their accuracy.
Artillery leaders reduces artillery dispersion and aim time which both scales with veterancy 15% for vet 1, 25% for vet 2, and 33% for vet 3.
